"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-lebron-james-team-usa-flag-bearer-2024-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Opening Ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympics is only days away, and as always, the host nation is planning a visual and auditory extravaganza to blow viewers away.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France is giving the world anOpening Ceremonythe likes of which it has never seen before, with athletes being sent on a river parade down the Seine.\", \"from\": 167, \"to\": 315, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 167, \"end\": 173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8068647642149862, \"rank\": 0.2380977612329797, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 309, \"end\": 314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999983424813857, \"rank\": 9.087340859931176e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the first time that an Olympics Opening Ceremony will not be held in a stadium, and fans will not want to miss it.\", \"from\": 316, \"to\": 438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As of 2020, every participating nation is allowed two flag bearers (one male and one female) for the Opening Ceremony.\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 541, \"end\": 557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.803977261592564, \"rank\": 0.23910905015861805, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being chosen to carry the flag is one of the greatest honors an athlete can receive, not only because these athletes get the chance to represent their country on such a tremendous stage but because the flag bearer is determined by a vote of their peers in a poll conducted by the Team USA Athletes' Commission.\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999954261127197, \"rank\": 4.555536138264249e-06, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are still waiting to find out which female athlete will represent the United States delegation, but the male flag bearer has been announced, and it's a name people might have heard of before.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 1065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 944, \"end\": 957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999941024524298, \"rank\": 5.015974149793382e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's right, LeBron James will be adding to his list of accolades by carrying the U.S. flag in the Opening Ceremony.\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1080, \"end\": 1092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 1149, \"end\": 1158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999868123, \"rank\": 1.329861292706979e-11, \"text\": \"U.S. flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"James is one of the greatest and most recognizable athletes in the world.\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1185, \"end\": 1190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 0.9999993102408203, \"rank\": 6.154499184685807e-07, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is little he has not done on the basketball court, both in the NBA, where he's won four MVPs and four championships and at the Olympics, where he's won a bronze medal (2004) and two golds (2008 and 2012).\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1328, \"end\": 1331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 2.9098102306094827e-12, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be his fourth Olympics, making him one of the senior members of the team, and it's a clear statement that the United States is there to win.\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1590, \"end\": 1603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999941024524298, \"rank\": 5.015974149793382e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For James, it's the latest milestone in a truly singular career.\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1626, \"end\": 1631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 0.9999993102408203, \"rank\": 6.154499184685807e-07, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's the first men's basketball player to represent the U.S. as a flag bearer, and he joins Dawn Staley and Sue Bird as the only other basketball players from this country to receive the honor.\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1880, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1779, \"end\": 1790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Staley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dawn Staley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Staley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Staley\"}, {\"begin\": 1795, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Bird\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sue Bird\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Bird\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Bird\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even as the quality of basketball around the world has greatly improved in the past couple of decades, the U.S. men's team is still a heavy favorite to once again win gold.\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 2054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1989, \"end\": 1993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9010036412678639, \"rank\": 0.10969180822263297, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, it's far from a sure thing, as Saturday's shockingly close tune-up game with South Sudan proved.James saved the U.S.from one of the most astonishing upsets in international basketball history by scoring 25 points and sinking a layup with eight seconds left to complete a 16-point comeback and secure a 101-100 U.S. win.\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"James has been in the headlines recently due to theLakers drafting his son Bronny, and for the ongoing conversation about whether retirement could be in the cards for him in the next couple of years.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2383, \"end\": 2388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 0.9999993102408203, \"rank\": 6.154499184685807e-07, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"James is still an extremely effective NBA player, but no matter how long his NBA career lasts, this will almost surely be his final Olympics.\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2724, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2583, \"end\": 2588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 0.9999993102408203, \"rank\": 6.154499184685807e-07, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 2621, \"end\": 2624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 2.9098102306094827e-12, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 2660, \"end\": 2663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 2.9098102306094827e-12, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carrying the flag and potentially leading another gold medal-winning run would be a heck of a way to go out.\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2\\u00a9 2026Minute Media-All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 2875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only.\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 2952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Minute Media or its affiliates and related brands.\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 3130, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit.\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3219, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\", \"from\": 3220, \"to\": 3352, \"entities\": []}]}"